Math Methods
    Syntax:
        Math.method(number)

    Number to Integer:
        • There are 4 common methods to round a number to an integer
            → Math.round(x) : Returns x rounded 
              to its nearest integer
            → Math.ceil(x) : Returns x rounded 
              up to its nearest integer
            → Math.floor(x) : Returns x rounded 
              down to its nearest integer
            → Math.trunc(x) : Returns the 
              integer part of x



    Math.sign()
        Math.sign(x) returns if x is negative, null or positive
            Math.sign(-4);//-1
            Math.sign(0);//0
            Math.sign(4);//1

    Math.pow()
        • Math.pow(x, y) returns the value of x to the power of y
            Math.pow(9, 2); //81

    Math.sqr()
        • Math.sqrt(x) returns the square root of x
            Math.sqrt(81);//9

    Math.abs()
        • Math.abs(x) returns the absolute (positive) value of x
            Math.abs(-5.98); //5.98

__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

    Min and Max Method
    Max - finding the max value
    Min - finding the min value

    console.log(Math.max(150,250,10,65,1050,1250,125)); //1250
    console.log(Math.min(150,250,10,65,1050,1250,125)); //10


    Random Method -> prints a random number

